<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return true if this shuffle mask is a transpose mask.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Transpose vector masks transpose a 2xn matrix. They read corresponding</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// even- or odd-numbered vector elements from two n-dimensional source</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// vectors and write each result into consecutive elements of an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// n-dimensional destination vector. Two shuffles are necessary to complete</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the transpose, one for the even elements and another for the odd elements.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This description closely follows how the TRN1 and TRN2 AArch64</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instructions operate.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, a simple 2x2 matrix can be transposed with:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   ; Original matrix</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   m0 = &lt; a, b &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   m1 = &lt; c, d &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   ; Transposed matrix</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   t0 = &lt; a, c &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1, &lt; 0, 2 &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   t1 = &lt; b, d &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1, &lt; 1, 3 &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For matrices having greater than n columns, the resulting nx2 transposed</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// matrix is stored in two result vectors such that one vector contains</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// interleaved elements from all the even-numbered rows and the other vector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// contains interleaved elements from all the odd-numbered rows. For example,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// a 2x4 matrix can be transposed with:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   ; Original matrix</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   m0 = &lt; a, b, c, d &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   m1 = &lt; e, f, g, h &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   ; Transposed matrix</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   t0 = &lt; a, e, c, g &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1 &lt; 0, 4, 2, 6 &gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   t1 = &lt; b, f, d, h &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1 &lt; 1, 5, 3, 7 &gt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/shufflevectorinst/#a28026e5094b94a512f9116384eed7c93"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/shufflevectorinst/#a28026e5094b94a512f9116384eed7c93">isTransposeMask</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef&lt;int&gt;</a> Mask, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NumSrcElts) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return true if this shuffle transposes the elements of its inputs without</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00866" /><CodeLine lineNumber="866"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return true if this shuffle mask represents &quot;clustered&quot; mask of size VF,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00867" /><CodeLine lineNumber="867"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// i.e. each index between &#91;0..VF) is used exactly once in each submask of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00868" /><CodeLine lineNumber="868"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// size VF.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00869" /><CodeLine lineNumber="869"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, the mask for \\p VF=4 is:</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return true if the mask interleaves one or more input vectors together.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// I.e. &lt;0, LaneLen, ... , LaneLen&#42;(Factor - 1), 1, LaneLen + 1, ...&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// E.g. For a Factor of 2 (LaneLen=4):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   &lt;0, 4, 1, 5, 2, 6, 3, 7&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// E.g. For a Factor of 3 (LaneLen=4):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   &lt;4, 0, 9, 5, 1, 10, 6, 2, 11, 7, 3, 12&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   &lt;0, 2, 6, 4, 1, 3, 7, 5&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="908"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="909"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// StartIndexes are the first indexes of each vector being interleaved,</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="911"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// E.g. &lt;4, -1, 2, 5, 1, 3&gt; (Factor=3): StartIndexes=&lt;4, 0, 2&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
